headline: Europeans draw divergent lessons from Trump's threats over Greenland
description: While the crisis over Greenland, coveted by Donald Trump, has prompted some EU member states to consider strategic autonomy, others still don't believe Europe can defend itself without the US.

description: Attorney General Pam Bondi said in a post on X that Don Lemon and several other people had been arrested on unspecified federal charges in connection with what she called a 'coordinated attack' on the Cities Church in St. Paul, the twin city of Minneapolis.

headline: China's crackdown on a village of defiant Christians

headline: Beehives, yachts and cattle: How France manages 'atypical' seized assets
description: As caseloads surge, France's asset recovery agency is grappling with an influx of unusual seizures, costly to store, tricky to sell and sometimes a legal maze.

description: The sweeping powers that the US president has granted himself through his Board of Peace serve only to discourage even the best intentions, observes Le Monde's columnist Gilles Paris.

'The only thing left to do is leave': Cuba pushed to the brink
description: 'Cuba, an island adrift' (2/3). Since the wave of unrest that swept the country in 2021, more than two million Cubans have fled. Those who remain on the island scrape by with varying degrees of success, as the exorbitant price of basic goods has become a source of inequality between those with nothing and those with access to foreign currency.

headline: Iran in collective shock after bloody crackdown
description: Even though internet access remains mostly cut off, a few openings have allowed the population to grasp the unprecedented violence unleashed on protesters: tens of thousands killed, mass arrests, hospitals under surveillance and overcrowded prisons.

headline: 'For sure': Two impromptu words by Macron go viral
description: During his speech at the World Economic Forum in Davos, the French president delivered a common English phrase – in a strong accent – that achieved global fame.
